      <abstract>
        <b>The article is devoted to the main components of scientific activity of Russian sociologist Yulia Yurievna Sinelina (1972–2013). She was a well-known researcher of secularization in Russia, particularly the problems of interaction between modern society and religion. Her special attention was devoted to the application of theoretical and methodological investigations in sociology of religion to the religious situation in Russia.</b>
